        "content": "<p>wingo opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/11772\">issue #11772</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Apologies for these bugs, but I like for things to be clear :)  So the WASI spec says:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Set the Method for the Request. Fails if the string present in a</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// `method.other` argument is not a syntactically valid method.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">func</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">method</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">result</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>If we take the approach in <a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/wasi-http/issues/178\">https://github.com/WebAssembly/wasi-http/issues/178</a>, then we define syntactic validity according to <a href=\"https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc9110.html#section-9.1\">RFC 9110 ยง9.1</a>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">token</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">token</span><span class=\"w\">          </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">tchar</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"kt\">char</span><span class=\"w\">          </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"!\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"#\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"$\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"%\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"&amp;\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"'\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"*\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                 </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"+\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"-\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\".\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"^\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"_\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"`\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"|\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"~\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                 </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">DIGIT</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ALPHA</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                 </span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">any</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">VCHAR</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">except</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">delimiters</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>OK, weird that \"!\" can be a method, but OK.</p>\n<p>Only, Wasmtime rejects the following method names: <code>#</code>, <code>$</code>, <code>%</code>, <code>&amp;</code>, and <code>'</code>.  The others work!</p>\n<p>What should change here, if anything? :)</p>\n</blockquote>",
